    "body": "Related: #39721\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n`vim.fs.dirname()` can return paths above filesystem roots.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nNow, `vim.fs.dirname()` properly handles:\r\n\r\n- `/`\r\n- Windows UNC roots (`//server/share`)\r\n- Windows device drive roots (`//?/C:/`)\r\n- Windows device UNC roots ( `//?/UNC/server/share)\r\n- Windows device volume roots (`//?/BootPartition/`)\r\n\r\n~~i hate windows~~\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-15T21:43:13Z",
