            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> * Windows UNC roots (`//server/share`)\r\n\r\nThis made me remember that [`//path` is valid syntax on some weird Unix systems](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16840916/what-is-path-how-is-it-different-from) (it's defined by POSIX). I'm not sure if any Unix system that Neovim supports has this mean anything (it's certainly not a thing on Linux), but you *may* want to consider it.",
