        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Oops! I found one small logic error on Unix. Any more than two leading slashes should get expanded down to a normal path:\r\n\r\n- `PurePosixPath('/').parent == PurePosixPath('/')`\r\n- `PurePosixPath('//').parent == PurePosixPath('//')`\r\n- `PurePosixPath('///').parent == PurePosixPath('/')`\r\n\r\nSo `vim.fs.dirname('///')` (or `'////'`, etc.) should be `'/'`, not `'//'`.\r\n\r\nJust fix that (and add a test for both `'///'` and `'////'` being `'/'`) and we should be good.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-13T20:48:50Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39724#issuecomment-4445098480",
            "id": 4445098480,
